  "prompt": "What are some lesser known but amazing mysteries?",
  "response": "Here are some fascinating but lesser-known mysteries:\n\n1. Voynich Manuscript\n- An undeciphered medieval book with unknown language/script\n- Filled with bizarre illustrations and no known translation\n\n2. Dyatlov Pass Incident\n- Nine Russian hikers died under extremely strange circumstances\n- Found partially undressed in freezing conditions with unexplained injuries\n\n3. Dancing Plague of 1518\n- Hundreds of people in Strasbourg, France, danced uncontrollably for days\n- Many danced until they collapsed or died\n\n4. Wow! Signal\n- A mysterious radio signal from space in 1977\n- Never repeated or explained, potentially extraterrestrial\n\n5. Taos Hum\n- A low-frequency sound heard in Taos, New Mexico\n- Only some people can hear it, source unknown\n\n6. Flannan Isles Lighthouse Mystery\n- Three lighthouse keepers vanished without explanation in 1900\n- No trace was ever found of them\n\n7. The Bog People\n- Perfectly preserved ancient human bodies found in European peat bogs\n- Many show signs of ritualistic murder\n\n8. Tunguska Event\n- Massive unexplained explosion in Siberia in 1908\n- Flattened 830 square miles of forest, cause still debated\n\nThese mysteries continue to intrigue researchers and enthusiasts worldwide.",
